I deleted a branch (default/features/XYZ) on github after merging a corresponding pull request into master on github. The deleted branch is (as expected) no longer available on github.com. In SourceTree I can still see the branch beneath the REMOTES nodes as (origin/default/features/XYZ) and can still checkout this deleted branch. But if I try too pull the latest changes, I get the following error:

 

{{git -c diff.mnemonicprefix=false -c core.quotepath=false fetch origin}}{{git -c diff.mnemonicprefix=false -c core.quotepath=false pull --no-commit origin default/features/XYZ}}
{{fatal: Couldn't find remote ref default/features/XYZ}}
{{Completed with errors, see above.}}
